	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg – Five police officers and one off-duty soldier were killed when a group of men attacked the Ngcobo police station between Mthatha and Queenstown in the Eastern Cape. According to the police, the unknown suspects entered the police station in the early hours of Wednesday morning and without warning, randomly opened fire on the members on duty. ALSO READ: Senior Limpopo cop killed, another seriously injured by gunmen "Three members were killed instantly in the community service centre. An off-duty soldier was also shot dead as the suspects were fleeing," Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo said. "The suspects made off with a police van, taking two other members. The bodies of both these members with gunshot wounds, were later found along the roadside, six kilometres from the police station. ALSO READ: Cop shot dead on Cape Town highway while escorting truck containing perlemoen "According to preliminary investigations, it appears that [the] members were shot execution style." More to follow. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  